\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs28\lang9 SkyeClip Help\par
\par
\cf2\f1\fs24 Overview\par
\cf0\b0\par
SkyeClip is a lightweight clipboard manager that stores your recent clips, lets you mark favorites, and provides quick access through the tray menu and hotkeys.\par
\cf2\b\par
Tray Menu\par
\cf0\b0 To make it easier to identify the type of content stored in each clip, SkyeClip adds small format indicators to the end of the preview text. Clips that contain Rich Text Format data will include the suffix <RTF>. Clips that contain HTML data will include the suffix <HTML>. These indicators appear only in the preview list to help you quickly understand what formats are available for each clip. The full Clip Viewer still shows the complete content using the appropriate viewer (plain text, rich text, HTML, image, or file list)\par
\cf2\b\par
Tray Menu HotKeys (Customizable)\par
\cf0\par
\b0\i <F>\par
Toggle Favorite\par
\i0 Marks or unmarks the selected clip as a Favorite. Favorited clips appear in the Favorites menu for quick access.\par
\b\par
\b0\i <V>\par
Show Clip Viewer\par
\i0 Opens the Clip Viewer,\f2  a compact companion window that displays the full contents of the selected clip.\par
\par
\i\f1\lang1033 <S>\i0\par
Show Scratch Pad\par
Opens the Scratch Pad with the selected clip appended to the current text, if any.\f2\lang9\par
\par
\cf2\b\f1 Favorites\par
\par
\cf0\b0 Favorites let you keep important clips accessible at all times.\par
\i How to use:\i0\par
- Press Spacebar on a clip\par
- Or right\f2\_click \f3\u8594?\f1  Toggle Favorite\par
- Favorites appear in their own menu for quick access\par
\cf2\b\lang9\par
Clip Viewer\par
\cf0\b0\par
The Clip Viewer displays the full text of the selected clip.\par
Useful for reading long clips without having to paste somewhere.\par
\i Features:\i0\par
- View full clip contents\par
- Keyboard shortcut <Ctrl+C> to copy to clipboard\par
\par
\cf2\b Scratch Pad\cf0\b0\f2\par
\par
Scratch Pad is a lightweight, always\_available editor built into SkyeClip. It\rquote s designed for quick notes, temporary text, code snippets, and anything you want to keep handy while working. Scratch Pad supports both Rich Text (RTF) and Plain Text, and you can import or export content at any time.\par
\par
